<div style="max-width:840px;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;">
<div class="hidden stagger-2">
<p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:28px;text-align:left;">
            Inspired by William Basinski's <em>Disintegration Loops</em> (2002). A magnetic tape loop plays while the tape physically deteriorates, recorded over four hours. The loops dissolve from music into noise — not metaphorically, but literally. The iron oxide flakes from the tape as it passes the playhead. Each pass removes a little more of the signal. The dissolution is the composition.
