<p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:monospace;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:10px;">IANNIS XENAKIS</p>
<p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.75;">Iannis Xenakis (1922–2001): architect, composer, theorist. Applied stochastic processes — Markov chains, Poisson distributions, Brownian motion — to music composition in the 1950s. His book <em>Formalized Music</em> (1963) is the mathematical foundation of algorithmic composition. Every parameter of a piece could be derived from probability functions. The composer sets the rules; chance fills the score.</p>
